SOFTWARE TOOLWORKS Inc. of Chatsworth, Calif., said it is offering 2,730,000 common shares at $10.50 each in a public offering managed by Montgomery Securities.
The offering is being made according to a registration statement declared effective Friday by the Securities and Exchange Commission.
Of the shares being offered, the computer software maker said, 1.7 million will be sold by the company and 1,030,000 will be sold by shareholders.
The underwriters have been granted an option to purchase as much as an additional 409,500 shares to cover overallotments. 

